roidhive.info/2016/05/android-build-intro-slider-app/#disqus_thread">Comments</a></span></div> </header><div class="post-single-content box mark-links entry-content"><div class="thecontent" itemprop="articleBody"><div style="float:left;margin:10px 10px 10px 0;"> <script async src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>  <ins class="adsbygoogle"
style="display:inline-block;width:336px;height:280px"
data-ad-client="ca-pub-9207768510467156"
data-ad-slot="1410361821"></ins> <script>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script> </div><p>Adding Welcome / Intro screens in your app is a great way of showcasing the major features of the app. Previously I explained about adding a static <a href="http://www.androidhive.info/2013/07/how-to-implement-android-splash-screen-2/" target="_blank">Splash Screen</a> to your app. In this article we are going to learn how to add an intro slider to your app where user can swipe through few slides before getting into app.</p><p>To demonstrate, I am creating a simple app that contains few intro slides with next and skip navigation. The user can navigate through each slide using swipe gesture or using the next button. I&#8217;ll also explain how to show the intro only when the app is launched for the first time.</p><div style="display:none"> <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="http://www.androidhive.info/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/android-welcome-intro-slider-with-bottom-dots.png" alt="android welcome intro slider with bottom dots" width="720" height="359" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39421" srcset="http://www.androidhive.info/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/android-welcome-intro-slider-with-bottom-dots-300x150.png 300w, http://www.androidhive.info/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/android-welcome-intro-slider-with-bottom-dots.png 720w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px" /><noscript><img src="http://www.androidhive.info/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/android-welcome-intro-slider-with-bottom-dots.png" alt="android welcome intro slider with bottom dots" width="720" height="359" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39421" srcset="http://www.androidhive.info/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/android-welcome-intro-slider-with-bottom-dots-300x150.png 300w, http://www.androidhive.info/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/android-welcome-intro-slider-with-bottom-dots.png 720w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px" /></noscript></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="download_code"> <a class="btn_left" href="http://download.androidhive.info/download?code=15Q0zcRENgXF8uJkHGK0D1D82prRw3NFFIv9YibekPpbaJxgf6GHqrFpaor%2BLKel%2F6kFCo%2FcwtxhTQ1FFmvOz%2FprpgSHvNjXfI4dMfQrqaUesxVC1U4BX%2BO7w%3D%3D1L9Qh2yw0j9Z8brdn9dy908BuI14sfy3zzD" target="_blank">DOWNLOAD CODE</a><a  class="btn_left" href="http://download.androidhive.info/apk/Intro_slider.apk" target="_blank">DOWNLOAD .APK</a></div><div class="yt_video"> <label>VIDEO DEMO</label><br /> <iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/yW1h44uPOg4" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="" style="width: 719px; height: 444.7265625px;"></iframe></div></p><p>Here is the final app we are going to build.</p><div class="image"> <img style="margin: 0 auto;" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="http://www.androidhive.info/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/android-welcome-slider-animation-with-dots.gif" alt="android welcome slider animation with dots" width="400" height="711" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39395" /><noscript><img style="margin: 0 auto;" src="http://www.androidhive.info/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/android-welcome-slider-animation-with-dots.gif" alt="android welcome slider animation with dots" width="400" height="711" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39395" /></noscript></div><p>Let&#8217;s start by creating a new project.</p><h2>1. Creating New Project</h2><p><strong>1</strong>. Create a new project in Android Studio from <strong>File â New Project</strong>. When it prompts you to select the default activity, select <strong>Empty Activity</strong> and proceed.</p><p><strong>2</strong>. Download this <a href="http://api.androidhive.info/welcome_slider/res.zip" target="_blank">res.zip</a> and add them to your projects <strong>res</strong> folder. This zip file contains few drawable images required for this app.</p><h3>2. Choosing the Colors</h3><p>It&#8217;s completely upto you how you design the intro screens considering the type of app you are building. For this example, I am placing a big image in centre and few texts below it. At the bottom, number of dots are placed indicating the number of slides it has.</p><p>Below is the color palette I have selected to design the screens. For every screen we need three colors i.e background color and two dot colors when it is active / inactive.</p><div class="image"> <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="http://www.androidhive.info/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/welcome-slider-color-pallete-1.png" alt="welcome slider color pallete " width="720" height="143" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39389" /><noscript><img src="http://www.androidhive.info/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/welcome-slider-color-pallete-1.png" alt="welcome slider color pallete " width="720" height="143" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39389" /></noscript></div><p><strong>3</strong>. Open <strong>colors.xml</strong> located under <strong>res â values</strong> and add the below color values. You can see after adding the colors, I have kept them into arrays <strong>array_dot_active</strong> and <strong>array_dot_inactive</strong>, so that we can load them easily in our activity.</p><pre class="brush: xml; title: colors.xml; notranslate" title="colors.xml">
&lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;utf-8&quot;?&gt;
&lt;resources&gt;
    &lt;color name=&quot;colorPrimary&quot;&gt;#3F51B5&lt;/color&gt;
    &lt;color name=&quot;colorPrimaryDark&quot;&gt;#303F9F&lt;/color&gt;
